
Step 1. Set up the Development Environment
-------------------------------------------
Install Node.jsÂ® and npm if they are not already on your machine.

c:\SWDTOOLS\node-v8.10.0-win-x64\etc\npmrc --- globally

proxy=http://user:pass@host:port/
https_proxy=https://user:pass@host:port/
registry=http://registry.npmjs.org/
strict-ssl=false
prefix=c:\SWDTOOLS\node_config\node_global
cache=c:\SWDTOOLS\node_config\node_cache
python=C:\SWDTOOLS\Python27\python.exe

Verify : node -v and npm -v

To install a version that will be released in the future, run:

npm install npm@latest -g
or
npm install npm@next -g.
        
Step 2. Install angular

npm install -g @angular/cli --- globally





